# Amazon EC2 (Elastic Compute Cloud)

Amazon EC2 (Elastic Compute Cloud) is AWS's Infrastructure as a Service (IaaS) offering. It provides resizable virtual servers in the AWS Cloud.

EC2 allows organizations to run applications without purchasing and maintaining physical hardware. Users can choose the required compute capacity, operating system, storage, networking configuration, and security settings.

---

# Main EC2 Capabilities

Amazon EC2 can be used for:

- Running virtual servers in the cloud.
- Hosting applications and websites.
- Running backend services.
- Processing workloads requiring scalable compute capacity.
- Connecting applications with AWS storage services.
- Scaling infrastructure automatically using Auto Scaling Groups.
- Distributing traffic using Elastic Load Balancers.

---

# EC2 Instance Configuration Options

When launching an EC2 instance, several components must be configured.

## Amazon Machine Image (AMI)

An AMI is a template used to create EC2 instances.

An AMI contains:

- Operating system.
- Installed software.
- Application configuration.
- System settings.

Types of AMIs:

- AWS provided AMIs.
- Community AMIs.
- Custom AMIs created by users.

Custom AMIs allow organizations to deploy identical servers quickly and consistently.

