# EC2 Storage Options

EC2 supports multiple storage options.

## Elastic Block Store (EBS)

Amazon EBS provides persistent block storage for EC2 instances.

Characteristics:

- Data remains after instance termination (depending on configuration).
- Can be attached and detached from instances.
- Commonly used for operating system disks and databases.

Examples:

- Boot volumes.
- Database storage.
- Application storage.

---

## EC2 Instance Store

Instance Store provides temporary local storage physically attached to the EC2 host.

Characteristics:

- Very high performance.
- Data is lost when the instance is stopped or terminated.
- Useful for temporary workloads.

Examples:

- Cache files.
- Temporary processing.
- High-performance workloads.

---

## Elastic File System (EFS)

Amazon EFS provides managed shared file storage.

Characteristics:

- Multiple EC2 instances can access the same files.
- Automatically scales storage capacity.
- Uses the NFS protocol.

Common use cases:

- Shared application files.
- Content management systems.
- Web servers requiring shared storage.

