# Security Groups vs Network ACLs

## Security Groups

- Stateful firewall.
- Applied to EC2 instances.
- Allow rules only.
- Return traffic automatically allowed.

## Network ACLs

- Stateless firewall.
- Applied at subnet level.
- Supports allow and deny rules.
- Return traffic must be explicitly allowed.

